Edition:
Quote:   [On Central Otago naming in c1860s] Frankton was called [by W.G.Rees] after Mrs. Rees' Christian name, Francis; ... the Shotover from Shotover Park, where Mr. Rees' partner, Mr. Gammie, formerly resided; ... and Moke Creek after old Donald, the first horse which fed upon its grassy banks.
